member.example:
This sample shows how to call PutAsync with required request content.

var client = new ValueTypesClient().GetModelClient("1.0.0");

var data = new {
    property = new {
        property = "<property>",
    },
};

Response response = await client.PutAsync(RequestContent.Create(data), new RequestContext());
Console.WriteLine(response.Status);

member.remarks:
Below is the JSON schema for the request payload.

Request Body:

Schema for ModelProperty:
{
  property: {
    property: string, # Required. Required string property
  }, # Required. Property
}

